    "IPlBOTikffqSEBo EDWAltlJSVILLE AUGUST 1 1820 It is said that Mr Kane has procured certi ficates from some of the gentlemen of this place who were referred to for the establish ment f certain facts in relation to the de velopemcnt of a plan to introduce slavery into this state which appeared in the Spectator of the 11th ult and that the substance of those certificates is 1 That all to which those gentlemen can testify relates to the establishment of a new press at this place to be edited by Gen Street fbr the purpose of advocating the introduction df slavery into this state 2 That they knew nothing in relation to Jfir Kanes being engaged in the plan A few remarks upon both of these points ftiay be necessary in order to give a correct Understanding of the subject As to the first independent of other proof that could be produced if necessary that Which relates to the establishment of a press ot this place for the purpose of advocating slavery taken in connection with other well known facts is sufficient proof of the most im portant parts of the statement referred to The intention to establish the press"
